CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 15, 1966, pg.1B reads:"Distinguished Ladies - One of the social highlights of the season among clubwomen was the 60th Anniversary Tea given by members of the Violet Art Club. Held at the St. James Church, among the distinguished ladies participating on program were left to right: Mrs. Mary L. Walker, past-president, City-Council Federation of Clubs; Mrs. Clara Bailey, past-president of Violet Art; Mrs. Lucille Chick, guest speaker; miss Dorothy Updyke, master of ceremonies; Mrs. Nancy Smith, honored guest, and Mrs. Mabel Stewart, past-president at Violet Art Club. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Six women, from left: Mary L. Walker, Clara Bailey, Lucille Chick, Dorothy Updyke, Nancy Smith, and Mabel Stewart, gathered in St. James AME Church for Violet Art Club sixtieth anniversary tea
